And here’s the new version of make_queue :
Queue *make_queue(int length)
{
Queue *queue = (Queue *) malloc(sizeof(Queue));
queue->length = length;
queue->array = (int *) malloc(length * sizeof(int));
queue->next_in = 0;
queue->next_out = 0;
queue->mutex = make_semaphore(1);
queue->items = make_semaphore(0);
queue->spaces = make_semaphore(length-1);
return queue;
}

mutex is used to guarantee exclusive access to the queue; the initial value is 1,
so the mutex is initially unlocked.
is the number of items in the queue, which is also the number of con-
items
sumer threads that can execute queue_pop without blocking. Initially there
are no items in the queue.
